The paper deals with decoding algorithms for discrete channels with or without memory, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The algorithm introduced in the paper involves ranking noise sequences and subtracting them from the received signal, which is a technique used in coding theory (cs.CC). The paper also discusses complexity and computational issues, which are relevant to computer science (cs.DS). The use of error and success exponents is a common approach in statistical inference and machine learning, which are subfields of computer science (cs.SI) and network information theory (cs.NI).
